    "body": "Hey, as discussed yesterday, I tried to run this case in `py_ecc`:\r\n```python\r\ndef test_privkey_830():\r\n    privkey = int.from_bytes(((830).to_bytes(48, 'little')), 'little')  # just try to reproduce your test; in py_ecc, the privkey is `int`.\r\n    assert privkey == 830\r\n    original = bls.privtopub(privkey)\r\n    print('original:', original.hex())\r\n    encoded = ssz.encode(original, ssz.sedes.bytes48)\r\n    print('encoded:', encoded.hex())  # bytes48 vector just returns the same input\r\n    decoded = ssz.decode(encoded, ssz.sedes.bytes48)\r\n    assert original == decoded\r\n    assert ssz.encode(original, ssz.sedes.bytes48) == ssz.encode(decoded, ssz.sedes.bytes48)\r\n    assert bls.utils.pubkey_to_G1(original) == bls.utils.pubkey_to_G1(decoded)\r\n    print('bls.utils.pubkey_to_G1(original:', bls.utils.pubkey_to_G1(original))\r\n```\r\n\r\nWe don't have API as `as_uncompressed_bytes`, so I only tried `pubkey_to_G1` instead.\r\n\r\nOutput\r\n```python\r\noriginal: 96e108a8ac7aa8522c4447f091f78cdc1814ddf31d3ea9fa6e605a3ff034763749fe53dcc357a1e9c156531af67f9631\r\nencoded: 96e108a8ac7aa8522c4447f091f78cdc1814ddf31d3ea9fa6e605a3ff034763749fe53dcc357a1e9c156531af67f9631\r\nbls.utils.pubkey_to_G1(original: (3521406296023103111408692011802051237538185282649417142853203752598594154949005629166201815771914073589371048531505, 661855166479205040239580294057573726944340033014371846511483552532122177247237805222474873068914205407884926981738, 1)\r\n```\r\n\r\nDo we get the same `pubkey` here?\r\n",
