    "body": "Hey guys, I just found out why this was happening it's because `int_to_bytes48()` converts it to little endian whereas `SecretKey::from_bytes()` is big endian. \r\n\r\nWhy the the conversion too / from uncompressed bytes occurs when fails when using little endian - 830 I'm not sure but my guess would be something funky happening as you have a secret key bigger than the curve order. Theoretically that shouldn't be an issue but we'll have to look into the amcl library `SecretKey::from_bytes()`",
